oai_dc:dc.dc:title: IMPORTANCE OF PERMABILITY IN THE SEDIMENTATION CONSOLIDATION PROCESS
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Alexis, A.
Thomas, P.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: sedimentation
consolidaiton
permeability
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: This paper first presents a literature review of permeability laws. A link between hydraulics and geotechnics formulations is pointed out. Second, reduced permeability expressions are discussed from experimental data available in literature. An extented exponential expression of reduced permeabilty is proposed.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Coastal Engineering Proceedings; No. 24 (1994): Proceedings of 24th Conference on Coastal Engineering, Kobe, Japan, 1994.
